  The keyword HASTA QUE was found, but the last open control structure was not a REPETIR structure. 
  * Check that your nested structures are correctly organized, that is, that their entry and exit points are well placed and that each one opens and closes at the same level.
  * Move HASTA QUE to where it belongs, or close the nested structures inside this REPETIR first.

112
  The keyword FINPROCESO was found, but the last open control structure was not a PROCESO structure. 
  * Check that your nested structures are correctly organized, that is, that their entry and exit points are well placed and that each one opens and closes at the same level.
  * Move FINPROCESO to where it belongs, or close the nested structures inside this PROCESO first.

114
  The set of instructions repeated by the PARA loop is delimited by the FINPARA keyword at the end of it. This PARA instruction does not have its corresponding FINPARA (or it is misplaced).
  * Check that the corresponding FINPARA exists for this PARA and that it is correctly written.
  * Remember that FINPARA is written together if your language <A href="perfiles.html">profile</A> does not allow flexible syntax (not FIN PARA).
  * Check that the nested control structures inside this PARA have been properly closed.

115
  The set of instructions repeated by the REPETIR-HASTA QUE loop is delimited by the keywords HASTA QUE and the exit condition at the end of it. This REPETIR instruction does not have its corresponding HASTA QUE (or it is misplaced).
  * Check that the corresponding HASTA QUE exists for this PARA and that it is correctly written.
  * Check that the nested control structures inside this PARA have been properly closed.
  * If your language <A href="perfiles.html">profile</A> allows flexible syntax, remember that the words REPETIR and HACER mark the beginning of a loop that must end with the constructions HASTA QUE... or MIENTRAS QUE...

116
  The set of instructions repeated by the MIENTRAS loop is delimited by the FINMIENTRAS keyword at its end. This MIENTRAS instruction does not have its corresponding FINMIENTRAS (or it is misplaced).
  * Check that the corresponding FINMIENTRAS exists for this MIENTRAS and that it is correctly written.
  * Remember that FINMIENTRAS is written together if your language <A href="perfiles.html">profile</A> does not allow flexible syntax (not FIN MIENTRAS).
  * Check that the nested control structures inside this MIENTRAS have been properly closed.
  * If you were trying to use the word "MIENTRAS" to close a REPETIR...MIENTRAS QUE or HACER...MIENTRAS QUE loop, you must replace it with "MIENTRAS QUE" to avoid the ambiguity produced with the MIENTRAS...FINMINETRAS loop. This is only possible if your <A href="perfiles.html">profile</A> allows flexible syntax.

117
  The set of instructions that may be executed by the SI-ENTONCES conditional structure is delimited by the FINSI keyword at its end. This SI instruction does not have its corresponding FINSI (or it is misplaced).
  * Check that the corresponding FINSI exists for this SI and that it is correctly written.
  * Remember that FINSI is written together if your language <A href="perfiles.html">profile</A> does not allow flexible syntax (not FIN SI).
  * Check that the nested control structures inside this SI have been properly closed.

118
  The set of instructions that may be executed by the SEGUN conditional structure is delimited by the FINSEGUN keyword at its end. This SEGUN instruction does not have its corresponding FINSEGUN (or it is misplaced).
