  The string passed as an argument to the ConvertirANúmero function does not contain a number. The string must contain only digits and optionally a dot to separate decimals, and a plus or minus sign at the beginning to indicate whether it is a positive or negative number, but it must not contain spaces, letters, or other signs or operators. 
  * Check that the value of that string (which is shown in parentheses in the error message) is a valid number.

